Feature: Bootstrap-generated top-level "CLAUDE.md" contains the router-side Monitor activation instruction

  Supersedes scenario d4b8aac19b34ea8c (features/templates/57-canonical-claude-settings-json-templates-ship-from-shop-templates.gherkin, currently pinned in repos/shopsystem-templates/features/brief_003_event_driven_activation_and_settings_json_bootstrap.feature from lead-xkh / brief 003) as hash 1621b59b0ea8b20b.

  Scenario 57 pinned ".claude/settings.json" as the shipping surface for activation. Brief 003's realization revision (lead-o00) retires that home: ".claude/settings.json" still ships from "shop-templates" (scenarios 74 and 75 pin its new minimal/bd-prime-only content for bc and lead respectively), but it is no longer the activation home. The activation home is the canonical "CLAUDE.md" primer (scenario 71 carries the canonical-side pin). This scenario carries the bootstrap-side pin: the activation instruction must land in the bootstrap output (not only in the canonical package data) so that a freshly-bootstrapped shop is reactive on its first session start.

  Structural parallel: this scenario mirrors scenario 53 (bootstrap-generated CLAUDE.md references bd discipline) for the activation instruction — the canonical content (scenario 71) is the source of truth, and the bootstrap output must reflect it.

  The Implementer should retire scenario 57's content from repos/shopsystem-templates/features/brief_003_event_driven_activation_and_settings_json_bootstrap.feature (BC-side hash 1621b59b0ea8b20b) when landing this scenario. Note that ".claude/settings.json" still ships from the canonical package-data surface — scenarios 74 and 75 pin its new content — so the package-data surface itself does not disappear; only its role as the activation home is retired.

  @scenario_hash:52c79a14592382ed
  Scenario Outline: the top-level "CLAUDE.md" that bootstrap writes into the target directory contains the router-side Monitor activation instruction for the shop type, so a freshly-bootstrapped shop is reactive on its first session start without depending on a SessionStart hook
    Given an existing git repository at a target directory "<target>" with no top-level "CLAUDE.md"
    When I invoke the "shop-templates" bootstrap entry point with shop type "<shop_type>", shop name "<shop_name>", and target directory "<target>"
    Then the exit code is 0
    And the target directory contains a top-level file named "CLAUDE.md"
    And the content of that file contains the literal substring "Monitor"
    And the content of that file contains the literal substring "session start"
    And the content of that file contains the literal substring "stdbuf -oL inotifywait"
    And the content of that file contains the literal substring "-m -e create,moved_to"
    And the content of that file contains the literal substring "<watch_target>"

    Examples:
      | shop_type | shop_name               | target                       | watch_target       |
      | bc        | shopsystem-messaging    | /tmp/example-bc-shop         | inbox/             |
      | lead      | shopsystem-product      | /tmp/example-lead-shop       | repos/*/outbox/    |
